<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8427&amp;p=87802#p87802"><![CDATA[
It's possible to design an HSL style color picker closely related to YUV, where the HS plane is essentially UV converted to polar as seen on <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vectorscope" class="postlink">vectorscopes</a>. That would put pure green at a higher lightness than pure blue, as you'd prefer.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Wed Dec 21, 2011 10:35 am</p><hr />
