<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=8427&amp;p=87727#p87727"><![CDATA[
I like HSL way better than RPG as it's more "human-eye friendly".<br /><br />If you are doing SNES-dev I'd consider using a HSL to RPG conversion program so you can pick the hue and brightness of all your colors and it's easier to get the color you want like that than by using R, G and B values.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Tue Dec 20, 2011 2:13 am</p><hr />
